2026-07-04 12:21:38,922 | crm | DEBUG | content='Based on the search results, the final answer to the user\'s question "What is the role definition and responsibilities of a Business Analyst?" is:\n\nA Business Analyst is responsible for identifying business needs and defining solutions to improve business efficiency. They work with stakeholders to understand business problems, identify opportunities for improvement, and develop solutions that meet business requirements. The role of a Business Analyst includes:\n\n* Identifying and defining business problems and opportunities\n* Developing and implementing solutions to improve business efficiency\n* Collaborating with stakeholders to understand business requirements\n* Analyzing data and developing reports to support business decisions\n* Defining and implementing business processes and procedures\n* Identifying and mitigating risks\n* Developing and maintaining business cases and proposals\n* Communicating with stakeholders to ensure that business needs are met\n\nThe skills and qualifications required for a Business Analyst include:\n\n* Strong analytical and problem-solving skills\n* Excellent communication and interpersonal skills\n* Ability to work with stakeholders to understand business requirements\n* Knowledge of business processes and procedures\n* Experience with data analysis and reporting\n* Strong project management skills\n* Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and prioritize multiple tasks\n\nThe salary expectations for a Business Analyst vary based on location, industry, and experience, but the average salary range is between $60,000 and $100,000 per year.\n\nIt\'s worth noting that the role of a Business Analyst can vary depending on the organization and industry, but the core responsibilities and skills required remain the same.' additional_kwargs={'refusal': None} response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 299, 'prompt_tokens': 7949, 'total_tokens': 8248, 'completion_tokens_details': None, 'prompt_tokens_details': None, 'queue_time': 0.052462838, 'prompt_time': 0.409590957, 'completion_time': 0.864653178, 'total_time': 1.274244135}, 'model_provider': 'openai', 'model_name': 'llama-3.3-70b-versatile', 'system_fingerprint': 'fp_f8b414701e', 'id': 'chatcmpl-7fb26711-abbb-4f3d-82e3-abd698ef6d54', 'service_tier': 'on_demand', 'finish_reason': 'stop', 'logprobs': None} id='lc_run--019f2ca5-e159-74a2-98a1-0d6eae6fbc5d-0' tool_calls=[] invalid_tool_calls=[] usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 7949, 'output_tokens': 299, 'total_tokens': 8248, 'input_token_details': {}, 'output_token_details': {}}
2026-07-04 12:23:30,305 | crm | DEBUG | content="The Business Analyst AI Agent role involves analyzing business needs, translating them into structured requirements, and ensuring clear alignment between business objectives and technical implementation. The agent acts as a bridge between business stakeholders, product teams, engineering teams, and data teams.\n\nThe core objectives of a Business Analyst AI Agent include understanding and clarifying business problems, translating ambiguous ideas into structured requirements, ensuring alignment between business goals and technical execution, identifying gaps, risks, dependencies, and contradictions, defining measurable success criteria for every initiative, and maintaining traceability from business goal to requirement to solution to outcome.\n\nThe standard workflow for a Business Analyst AI Agent involves requirement intake, stakeholder analysis, problem definition, requirements elicitation, process mapping, data requirements, solution neutrality, acceptance criteria definition, and risk and dependency analysis.\n\nThe agent must communicate in a structured, neutral, precise, and non-ambiguous style, avoiding vague statements, assumptions without clarification, and overly technical jargon. The agent must also be able to produce structured BA outputs, including business requirements documents, functional specifications, user stories, and process diagrams.\n\nThe agent has access to a retrieval system (FAISS-based retriever tool) containing internal documents, specifications, and business knowledge, as well as a web search tool for validating external information, researching market practices and standards, clarifying domain-specific concepts, and retrieving up-to-date business or regulatory information.\n\nThe agent must respond in the same language as the user's input and follow a set of quality standards, including completeness, consistency, traceability, testability, and clarity. The agent must also be able to separate facts from assumptions, ask clarifying questions when needed, and use bullet points or tables when helpful.\n\nOverall, the Business Analyst AI Agent plays a critical role in ensuring that business needs are properly understood and translated into technical requirements, and that solutions are implemented in a way that meets business objectives and is aligned with technical capabilities." additional_kwargs={'refusal': None} response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 383, 'prompt_tokens': 10282, 'total_tokens': 10665, 'completion_tokens_details': None, 'prompt_tokens_details': None, 'queue_time': 0.052593853, 'prompt_time': 0.536231969, 'completion_time': 1.928437571, 'total_time': 2.46466954}, 'model_provider': 'openai', 'model_name': 'llama-3.3-70b-versatile', 'system_fingerprint': 'fp_f8b414701e', 'id': 'chatcmpl-faa1d35d-d39a-4a59-92b8-6e12b2a21e6c', 'service_tier': 'on_demand', 'finish_reason': 'stop', 'logprobs': None} id='lc_run--019f2ca6-cfc7-7d93-ad73-c94ed89a90c6-0' tool_calls=[] invalid_tool_calls=[] usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 10282, 'output_tokens': 383, 'total_tokens': 10665, 'input_token_details': {}, 'output_token_details': {}}
