2026-07-04 13:37:19,114 | crm | DEBUG | content="There are several business analysis tools and techniques that can be used to improve business decision-making and problem-solving. Some examples include:\n\n1. SWOT analysis: This involves identifying a business's strengths, weaknesses, opportunities, and threats to make informed decisions.\n2. PESTLE analysis: This involves analyzing external factors that could influence a business, such as political, economic, social, technological, legal, and environmental factors.\n3. Stakeholder analysis: This involves identifying and analyzing the needs and expectations of various stakeholders, such as customers, employees, and investors.\n4. Surveys: These can be used to gather information from customers, employees, or other stakeholders to inform business decisions.\n5. Personal and company visions: These can be used to clarify and communicate the goals and objectives of a business.\n\nThese tools and techniques can help businesses identify areas for improvement, assess risks, and streamline operations, leading to improved efficiency and profitability. Case studies can also provide real-world examples of how business analysts solve problems and implement strategies, which can help improve business analysis skills." additional_kwargs={'refusal': None} response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 213, 'prompt_tokens': 4222, 'total_tokens': 4435, 'completion_tokens_details': None, 'prompt_tokens_details': None, 'queue_time': 0.051176561, 'prompt_time': 0.271555052, 'completion_time': 0.562104729, 'total_time': 0.833659781}, 'model_provider': 'openai', 'model_name': 'llama-3.3-70b-versatile', 'system_fingerprint': 'fp_f8b414701e', 'id': 'chatcmpl-d2f32572-47fc-4ac8-bb94-97f5428c18f5', 'service_tier': 'on_demand', 'finish_reason': 'stop', 'logprobs': None} id='lc_run--019f2cea-ef64-7a90-8f77-86130976a977-0' tool_calls=[] invalid_tool_calls=[] usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 4222, 'output_tokens': 213, 'total_tokens': 443