2026-07-05 13:27:15,377 | crm | DEBUG | {'input': 'Give an analysis of construction industry of India. Search new data in internet.', 'output': '### Analysis of the Construction Industry in India (2024-2029)\n\n#### Overview\nThe construction industry in India is a significant contributor to the nation’s economic growth, accounting for around 8% of the total GDP in 2024. The sector is projected to expand robustly due to various macroeconomic factors and government initiatives.\n\n#### Market Growth and Projections\n- The construction market is expected to grow at a **compound annual growth rate (CAGR)** of approximately **6.4%** in real terms by **2026**.\n- By **2026**, the market size is projected to reach around **USD 0.79 trillion**, with further growth anticipated to **USD 1.10 trillion by 2031**.\n\n#### Key Drivers\n1. **Government Investment**: Increased capital expenditure in the **FY2026-27 budget**, representing **3.1% of GDP**, which indicates a **11.5% increase** from the previous fiscal year.\n2. **Infrastructure Development**: Significant investments in transport infrastructure and energy projects are driving construction activities.\n3. **Private Sector Participation**: Enhanced private capital involvement is expected to bolster market growth.\n\n#### Sector Performance\n- The construction industry in India expanded by **7.8%** in real terms in **2024**.\n- The **industrial production index** for infrastructure and construction goods showed a **9.1% increase** year-on-year in **2025**, indicating robust demand.\n\n#### Challenges\n- Despite growth, challenges such as regulatory hurdles, labor shortages, and rising material costs could impact the speed of expansion.\n\n#### Conclusion\nThe construction industry in India is positioned for strong growth driven by strategic government investments and increased private sector participation. However, stakeholders must navigate potential challenges to fully capitalize on the opportunities within this sector.\n\n### References\n- [Mordor Intelligence Report](https://www.mordorintelligence.com/industry-reports/india-construction-market)\n- [Research and Markets](https://www.researchandmarkets.com/report/india-construction-market)\n- [Ken Research](https://www.kenresearch.com/industry-reports/india-construction-market)'}
