ting. Mediterranean better value. UK losing badly post-Brexit expensive.\n\nInvestment Exodus:\n\nDevelopments cancelled. Investors withdrawing. Banks refusing finance. Private equity exiting. Future capacity eliminated.\n\nGovernment Failure:\n\nNo strategy. Tax uncompetitive. Visa complex expensive. Infrastructure neglected. Industry ignored.\n\nLong-Term Damage:\n\n5-10 years recovery IF crisis ends today. Permanent loss 20-30% infrastructure. Regional economies never recovering. Workers leaving permanently. Hotels converting residential.\n\nTruth:\n\nUK took tourism for granted. No resilience. Over-relied foreign visitors. Policy failures worsened crisis. Former strength now vulnerability.\n\nFuture: 2-3 years before recovery begins best case. Permanent smaller poorer domestic-only market likely.\n\nSOURCES: Heathrow data, hotel filings, VisitBritain stats, ONS employment\n\nDATA: 18% decline | 40 closures | 22% US down | 65% China down | £2.8bn lost | 30% vacancy\n\n#UKTourism #TourisrCrisis #Hotels #Economy #Hospitality #Documentary\n\n💬 Work in UK tourism? Share what you're seeing.\n\n£200bn industry collapsing in real-time.\n49 comments\n", 'score': 0.81489426, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://store.mintel.com/report/uk-domestic-tourism-market-report', 'title': 'UK Domestic Tourism Market Report 2025 | Mintel Store', 'content': "* We offer report subscriptions, **giving you access to all reports across entire categories** Find out more. Buy any four or more reports and save 20% off the total purchase price. UK Domestic Tourism Market Report 2025. Country cottages, wellness breaks and ‘slow travel' touring holidays are seeing rising demand as consumers seek restorative staycations in a time of economic gloom, rapid technological change and global uncertainty. ## UK Domestic Tourism Industry – Trends and Insights. * **Warm UK weather in 2025 has helped slow the market decline of recent years**, but domestic tourism remains sensitive to the rising cost of